.TH "ata_port_pbar_desc" 9 "ata_port_pbar_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_port_pbar_desc \- append PCI BAR description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_port_pbar_desc
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ","
.BI "ssize_t offset "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
target ATA port
.IP "bar" 12
target PCI BAR
.IP "offset" 12
offset into PCI BAR
.IP "name" 12
name of the area

If \fIoffset\fP is negative, this function formats a string which
contains the name, address, size and type of the BAR and
appends it to the port description.  If \fIoffset\fP is zero or
positive, only name and offsetted address is appended.

LOCKING:
None.
